▫️Day 17 – Auto-Restart ML API with Docker

▫️Steps
1. Stopped existing container: `docker stop <id>`
2. Restarted with auto-restart:

docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name titanic-api --restart=always titanic-flask-app

3. Verified by killing container and checking auto-restart
4. Optional: rebooted EC2 → container still runs

▫️Outcome
🔹ML API container now auto-recovers from crash or server reboot  
🔹Learned about Docker `--restart` policies (always, unless-stopped, on-failure)  
🔹Another step towards production-ready ML deployment
